description: North Carolina election officials have said early voting would start as planned on Oct. 17. But they don't know how many voting sites might be unusable in the swing state because of Hurricane Helene.
title: Hurricane Helene upends election planning in some parts of North Carolina

description: Gov. Tim Walz and Sen. JD Vance will take the debate stage tonight starting at 9 p.m. Watch the CBS News Vice Presidential Debate Simulcast on NPR.
title: Watch the CBS News Vice Presidential Debate Simulcast On NPR

description:
Iran launched long-range missiles against Israel, just hours after Israeli forces launched a ground offensive into southern Lebanon against Iran's main proxy, Hezbollah. The dramatic escalation is raising fears of an all-out war in the Middle East. We hear from two NPR correspondents in the region.

For more coverage of all sides of this conflict, go to npr.org/mideastupdates
title: Israel Invades Lebanon, Iran Attacks Israel

description: Amos starred as the family patriarch on the hit 1970s sitcom “Good Times" and earned an Emmy nomination for his role in the seminal 1977 miniseries “Roots."
title: John Amos, star of TV's 'Good Times' and 'Roots,' dies at 84

description: In his first nonfiction book in a decade, Coates reflects on what he learned while visiting three different places: Senegal, South Carolina and the Israeli-occupied West Bank.
title: Ta-Nehisi Coates explores how oppression can breed oppression in ‘The Message’

description: Jeep is recalling more than 194,000 plug-in hybrid SUVs because they can catch fire with the ignition turned off. The automaker says the risk of fire is reduced when the battery charge is depleted.
title: Jeep recalls 194,000 plug-in hybrid SUVs over fire risk

description: Vance’s former Democratic opponent, Tim Ryan, says the Ohio senator is likely to aggressively attack Harris-Walz during the debate Tuesday night to appeal to Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump.
title: JD Vance’s performance has audience of one: Trump, says former debate opponent

description: Colin Kaepernick and Nessa Diab wrote a new children’s book inspired by affirmations they share with their daughter and scores of young people they meet through their activism.
title: Colin Kaepernick and Nessa Diab wrote ‘We Are Free, You and Me’ with daughter in mind

description: Lebanese Prime Minister Najib Mikati said his country was facing “one of the most dangerous phases of its history” amid Israel’s ground incursion into southern Lebanon, which began late Monday.
title: Lebanon's government urges international community for support amid Israel’s invasion

description: This year, filmmaker Sterlin Harjo, poet Jericho Brown and disability rights activist Alice Wong are among the recipients of the so-called "genius grants." Each fellow receives $800,000.
title: Here's who made the 2024 MacArthur Fellows list

description: Shailaja Paik faced prejudice because of her family's Dalit caste and her gender. As a historian she's written ground-breaking books on India's Dalits and is now a MacArthur 'genius grant' awardee.
title: This new MacArthur “genius” says she defied caste prejudice thanks to Dad and Mom

description: The threat comes as Israel launches a ground incursion against the Iran-backed militant group Hezbollah in southern Lebanon. Israel killed longtime Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah in airstrikes last week.
title: Iran is poised to attack Israel, officials say, fueling Mideast turmoil

description: A bus carrying young students and their teachers on a school trip caught fire in suburban Bangkok, leaving more than 20 feared dead, officials and rescuers said.
title: More than 20 students and teachers are feared dead in Thailand school trip bus fire

description: JD Vance and Tim Walz will have their first vice presidential debate tonight as both parties aim to win over swing state voters. And, Israel invades Lebanon for the first time since 2006.
title: What to know about tonight's VP debate. And, a guide to discussing misinformation

description: In Nevada, 1 in 5 potential voters are Latino. That is a voting bloc with a lot of political power in a state where elections are won by a few percentage points. And campaigns are paying attention.
title: In Nevada, Latinos could pick the next president. They aren't sold on either candidate

description: Claudia Sheinbaum is a 62-year old environmental scientist who left academia on a political trajectory that took her from a local mayor, to running Mexico City, to winning the presidency with nearly 60 percent of the vote.
title: 5 things to know about Mexico's first female president

description: For the first time since 1996, both major parties have picked a veteran for vice president -- a fact that some veterans' groups are hoping it leads to greater understanding of military and vet issues.
title: Vance and Walz are both veterans. Here's what it means to have a vet VP

description: The Justice Department's third-in-command talked about the department's pledge to fight hate crimes, and shared he was close in age to Matthew Shepard, whose death inspired a federal law helping to prosecute people fueled by hate.
title: Justice Department No. 3 official pledges to fight hate crimes, fueled by personal story

description: As China marks 75 years of Communist rule, a battle is playing out over a Party insider's old notebooks and letters stored at Stanford University.
title: In battle over its past, China wages courtroom fight in California

description: Former President Jimmy Carter is turning 100. Here are images from notable events or parts of his life, both during his presidency and after.
title: Photos: As Jimmy Carter celebrates his 100th birthday, a look through the decades

description: As the presidential race ramps up in Georgia, one vital voting demographic is mobilizing and hoping to impact the race: young people.
title: How young Republicans and Democrats are whipping up votes in key districts

description: Republican Ohio Sen. JD Vance is prolific on the campaign trail with speeches and talking to reporters, but his messaging has at times been overshadowed by controversy often of his own making.
title: JD Vance’s time on the trail has often been overshadowed by self-made controversy

description: Nebraska has a unique solution to staffing elections: It allows counties to draft workers. Omaha's Douglas County is the only one to regularly use it. Here’s how the jury duty-like system works.
title: Poll workers can be hard to find. In Nebraska, election officials can draft them

description: Street fentanyl has long been viewed as unstoppable. Now many experts say the supply of the deadly synthetic opioid is suddenly drying up in many parts of the U.S. and fatal overdoses are dropping.
title: The pipeline of deadly fentanyl into the U.S. may be drying up, experts say

description: As states around it were passing bathroom bills and trans health care bans, Minnesota, under Gov. Tim Walz, went in the other direction, protecting transgender rights.
title: Tim Walz’s state became a ‘trans refuge.’ Here’s what that means and how it happened

description: Nora Durkin called a hotline to report abuse she says she experienced as a child. The woman who answered gave her the validation she had needed for years.
title: When she called a hotline to report abuse, the voice on the other end offered hope

description: Ishiba, who chosen as the ruling Liberal Democratic Party's new leader on Friday, replaces Fumio Kishida who stepped down after his government was dogged by multiple scandals.
title: Japan’s parliament elects Shigeru Ishiba as prime minister

description: Mutombo spent his retirement on humanitarian causes. He spoke nine languages and founded the Dikembe Mutombo Foundation, concentrating on improving the quality of life for people in the Congo.
title: Dikembe Mutombo, a Hall of Fame player and tireless advocate, dies at 58

description: Union dockworkers at ports across the U.S. began walking picket lines early Tuesday, threatening to halt the movement of billions of dollars' worth of goods.
title: Dockworkers begin walking picket lines, risking to snarl East and Gulf Coast ports
